Sentencas: An excellent oxide ion conductivity with high oxygen transportation of lanthanum silicate apatite at the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) can be achieved through the solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The doped La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-delta (x = 0.2 and 0.4) materials sintered at 1600 degrees C accomplished crystallinity and crystal structure of apatite-type.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The structural and electrochemical characterizations of La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-delta (x = 0.2 and 0.4) were executed using X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDX), and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) measurements.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The total oxide ion conductivities of La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-delta (x = 0.2 and 0.4) were measured from low to intermediate operating temperature range (450 to 800 degrees C) using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: Room temperature XRD patterns of La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-delta (x = 0.2 and 0.4) exhibited La10Si6O27 apatite phase with space group P6(3)/m as the main phase with the minor appearance of La2SiO5 as an impurity phase.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The highest total oxide ion conductivity of 3.24 x 10(-3) Scm(-1) and corresponding activation energy of 0.30 eV at 800 degrees C were obtained for La10Si5.6Al0.2Zn0.2O26.7 which contains a low concentration of Al3+ dopant.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Properties of Lanthanum Silicate Apatites La10Si6-x-0.2AlxZn0.2O27-δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs)
